derived from the retarded solutions in the Lorenz gauge with a point charge source, find the well-
known expressions for the electric and magnetic fields, and the proceed to show that Faraday's
law is not obeyed! Apparently the authors believe only selectively in the mathematics of
differentiation. If one substitutes the definitions (1) into the first equation of (2) one finds
